A group of doctors from seven countries – Pakistan, India, Iran, Afghanistan, Syria, Lebanon and Iraq has written a letter to President Muhammadu Buhari pointing to Sheikh Ibrahim El-Zakzaky’s physical conditions, and asking the Nigerian government to transfer him to a well-equipped hospital as soon as possible. The letter revealed El-Zakzaky’s medical and health status which required urgent attention. The names of the doctors were also listed in the letter as reported by FARS News Agency of Iran. Read the full text of the letter on FARS News Agency